UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: More children, including the most marginalized , are surviving, healthy, well nourished and developing to their full potential in their early years, with focus on the first 1,000 days

description.narrative: With UNICEF’s substantial support, the Multisectoral Action Plan for Nutrition was approved by the President of the Republic of Tajikistan, which unifies and guides multisectoral government ministries to work towards nutrition results. UNICEF’s support to the Ministry of Health and Social Protection strengthened supportive supervision and monitoring of the Integrated Management of Acute Malnutrition programme which resultedin 6,958 children with severe acute malnutrition treated and cured.Development and roll out of a real-time web-based monitoring system for salt iodization was successfully piloted to improve effectiveness and efficiency of external and internal quality control and quality assurance for salt iodization. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2022
